{"id":"toc-22","paragraphs":[{"elements":[{"attrs":{"b":true,"heavy_header":true},"type":"text","text":"Article 2"}]},{"elements":[{"attrs":{"b":true,"heavy_header":true},"type":"text","text":"THE TRANSMISSION OF DIVINE REVELATION "}]},{"elements":[{"type":"ref-ccc","ref_number":74},{"type":"text","text":"God \"desires all men to be saved and to come to the knowledge of the truth\":"},{"type":"ref","number":29},{"type":"text","text":" that is, of Christ Jesus."},{"type":"ref","number":30},{"type":"text","text":" Christ must be proclaimed to all nations and individuals, so that this revelation may reach to the ends of the earth:"}]},{"elements":[{"type":"text","text":"God graciously arranged that the things he had once revealed for the salvation of all peoples should remain in their entirety, throughout the ages, and be transmitted to all generations."},{"type":"ref","number":31}],"attrs":{"indent":true}}],"footnotes":{"29":{"number":29,"refs":[{"text":"⇒ 1 Tim 2:4","link":"http://www.vatican.va/archive/ENG0839/_P110.HTM#NTLET.1TIM.2.4"}]},"30":{"number":30,"refs":[{"text":"cf. ⇒ Jn 14:6","link":"http://www.vatican.va/archive/ENG0839/_PXM.HTM#GOSP.JOH.14.6"}]},"31":{"number":31,"refs":[{"text":"DV 7","link":null},{"text":"cf. ⇒ 2 Cor 1:20","link":"http://www.vatican.va/archive/ENG0839/_PZN.HTM#NTLET.2COR.1.20"},{"text":"⇒ 3:16 - ⇒ 4:6","link":"http://www.vatican.va/archive/ENG0839/_PZP.HTM#NTLET.2COR.3.16"}]}}}